345
00:16:38,701 --> 00:16:41,209
She's new at this, remember?
Go easy on her.

346
00:16:41,334 --> 00:16:42,916
I want you to show
me the side of you

347
00:16:43,252 --> 00:16:45,669
that wants to unchain herself
from the classroom,

348
00:16:45,839 --> 00:16:46,837
from the fiance

349
00:16:47,256 --> 00:16:49,275
that's stopping you
from being the person

350
00:16:49,468 --> 00:16:51,967
you really want to be.
I am the person I want to be.

351
00:16:52,137 --> 00:16:53,242
Come on.

352
00:16:53,367 --> 00:16:54,595
Nobody really wants

353
00:16:55,015 --> 00:16:56,930
to teach public school
and marry some guy

354
00:16:57,100 --> 00:16:58,641
who can't even pay the bills!

355
00:16:58,894 --> 00:17:00,351
Come on.

356
00:17:00,604 --> 00:17:02,142
You're just afraid of the unknown.

357
00:17:02,356 --> 00:17:04,075
All right, that's it.
You know what? That guy

358
00:17:04,274 --> 00:17:06,476
is someone I love, and that
classroom is my passion.

359
00:17:06,601 --> 00:17:08,567
Even on the hardest days,
at least I know I'm

360
00:17:08,821 --> 00:17:10,653
following my heart.
That's a lot more

361
00:17:10,823 --> 00:17:12,738
than I can say about you.
Sweetheart,

362
00:17:12,908 --> 00:17:14,975
why don't we go for a walk
and unwind a little bit?

363
00:17:15,100 --> 00:17:16,943
Somebody get her a benzo, ASAP.

364
00:17:17,068 --> 00:17:18,224
Forget it, I quit.

365
00:17:28,267 --> 00:17:29,376
You have a minute?

366
00:17:29,501 --> 00:17:31,257
Now is not actually a good time.

367
00:17:31,534 --> 00:17:33,008
You okay?

368
00:17:34,200 --> 00:17:35,934
Just on my way to
a business meeting.

369
00:17:41,100 --> 00:17:42,975
So, um...

370
00:17:43,100 --> 00:17:44,676
David, if your offer still stands,

371
00:17:44,801 --> 00:17:46,975
I... I'd actually like to
take you up on that loan.

372
00:17:47,100 --> 00:17:49,275
We can organize a payment plan.

373
00:17:49,400 --> 00:17:51,820
Money's yours. Just give me
a couple of days to make it happen.

374
00:17:52,133 --> 00:17:54,776
Thank you... so much.

375
00:17:54,901 --> 00:17:56,634
No worries.

376
00:18:03,133 --> 00:18:05,367
Studying to be an architect?

377
00:18:07,234 --> 00:18:08,336
That?

378
00:18:08,667 --> 00:18:10,296
No, it's just some property

379
00:18:10,534 --> 00:18:12,142
I'm thinking about acquiring.
Really?

380
00:18:13,400 --> 00:18:15,427
Beverly Hills mansion.
I knew you had money, but...

381
00:18:15,595 --> 00:18:17,920
I'm just looking for now.
Putting my feelers out there

382
00:18:18,045 --> 00:18:19,305
for some investment opportunities.

383
00:18:19,601 --> 00:18:21,975
Since when has flipping
multi-million dollar real estate

384
00:18:22,300 --> 00:18:23,435
been a hobby of yours?

385
00:18:23,734 --> 00:18:26,367
Since... forever.

386
00:18:31,834 --> 00:18:33,242
Is something wrong, David?

387
00:18:35,033 --> 00:18:37,657
You in trouble?
'Cause if you are, you can tell me.

388
00:18:37,825 --> 00:18:39,159
Nobody's in any trouble.

389
00:18:39,434 --> 00:18:40,618
Now, uh...

390
00:18:40,901 --> 00:18:42,901
do you mind?

391
00:18:44,100 --> 00:18:45,934
I got to get ready.

392
00:18:49,200 --> 00:18:51,743
Okay. So...

393
00:18:51,868 --> 00:18:53,476
that little paper thingy you signed?

394
00:18:53,601 --> 00:18:55,342
Yeah, that was a contract.

395
00:18:55,467 --> 00:18:56,476
You can't leave.

396
00:18:56,601 --> 00:18:58,342
I didn't sign off
on being humiliated.

397
00:18:58,467 --> 00:19:00,847
If this is what being a model
is about, it's not for me.

398
00:19:00,972 --> 00:19:03,433
Okay, look. Anton is on his way,
and if you're not here,

399
00:19:03,667 --> 00:19:05,142
then I get an ass-whipping,

400
00:19:05,267 --> 00:19:06,811
and it turns into a PR nightmare.

401
00:19:07,067 --> 00:19:08,938
That is all you care about,
isn't it?

402
00:19:09,267 --> 00:19:10,476
Furthering your career.

403
00:19:10,601 --> 00:19:12,108
Hey, I meant what I said

404
00:19:12,276 --> 00:19:14,402
in there, okay?
It's your choice

405
00:19:14,634 --> 00:19:16,042
if you don't want to
believe in yourself.

406
00:19:16,167 --> 00:19:18,698
Since when does believing in myself
require me to abandon all self-respect?

407
00:19:18,901 --> 00:19:21,576
Do you think Jonah's self-respect

408
00:19:21,834 --> 00:19:23,869
soars through the roof
every time he shoots

409
00:19:24,067 --> 00:19:25,509
a Dora the Explorer-
themed birthday bash?

410
00:19:25,634 --> 00:19:27,332
No! It's called compromise, Riley.

411
00:19:27,567 --> 00:19:29,709
You know what, just stop.
I don't trust you.

412
00:19:29,834 --> 00:19:31,109
I have never trusted you,

413
00:19:31,234 --> 00:19:33,875
and I am not having
this conversation with you.

414
00:19:34,000 --> 00:19:36,925
Well, have fun
having it with your fiancs, then,

415
00:19:37,167 --> 00:19:39,242
when you tell him you blew it today.

416
00:19:39,367 --> 00:19:40,476
I mean, really?

417
00:19:40,601 --> 00:19:41,930
Giving up on ten grand

418
00:19:42,167 --> 00:19:44,567
because of a little ego bruise?

419
00:19:46,334 --> 00:19:48,109
Kind of says a lot about the way

420
00:19:48,234 --> 00:19:50,634
things work at home, doesn't it?

421
00:20:03,501 --> 00:20:04,542
You heading out?

422
00:20:04,667 --> 00:20:06,743
Yeah. That killer lunch rush.

423
00:20:06,868 --> 00:20:07,975
Just hoping my legs will hold

424
00:20:08,100 --> 00:20:09,342
till I get to the bus stop.

425
00:20:09,467 --> 00:20:11,125
I can take you home if you want.

426
00:20:11,293 --> 00:20:12,627
On your motorcycle?

427
00:20:12,795 --> 00:20:16,005
Only if you appreciate that a Triumph
is so much more than a motorcycle.

428
00:20:16,234 --> 00:20:18,042
Auggie, I... I don't want
to take your helmet.

429
00:20:18,167 --> 00:20:19,242
Are you kidding me?

430
00:20:19,367 --> 00:20:20,809
You think I'd ever let
anything happen to you?

431
00:20:20,934 --> 00:20:22,434
Come on. Let's go.

432
00:20:26,634 --> 00:20:29,394
I loved how you played with shadows.

433
00:20:29,701 --> 00:20:31,209
Well, that whole last sequence,
that was lit

434
00:20:31,334 --> 00:20:32,843
by one super-long string
of Christmas lights.

435
00:20:32,968 --> 00:20:35,483
What? Yeah.
It wasn't going to work, I didn't think,

436
00:20:35,801 --> 00:20:37,309
'cause the Santa bulbs
kept getting in the way,

437
00:20:37,434 --> 00:20:39,988
but it actually...
it, uh, turned out really cool.

438
00:20:40,334 --> 00:20:41,542
Well, look, Jonah,

439
00:20:41,667 --> 00:20:43,376
you're obviously passionate
about your vision,

440
00:20:43,501 --> 00:20:45,008
and as the voice in Andrew's ear,

441
00:20:45,133 --> 00:20:48,367
I want to make sure he knows
exactly what that vision is.

442
00:20:51,921 --> 00:20:54,210
Thank you so much. I mean,

443
00:20:54,790 --> 00:20:57,318
this movie is pretty much my life.

444
00:20:58,200 --> 00:20:59,576
Movies in general are my life.

445
00:20:59,701 --> 00:21:00,809
Hooked the moment I saw

446
00:21:00,934 --> 00:21:03,409
Chitty Chitty Bang
Bang at the Ritz Five.

447
00:21:03,534 --> 00:21:05,471
Wait. What?

448
00:21:05,834 --> 00:21:07,140
The Ritz Five in Philly?

449
00:21:07,501 --> 00:21:08,975
You've been there?

450
00:21:09,300 --> 00:21:10,476
Kendra, that's where I'm from.

451
00:21:10,601 --> 00:21:12,312
- What?
- I'm from Philly.

452
00:21:12,480 --> 00:21:14,772
The Ritz Five is one of my favorite
movie theaters of all time.

453
00:21:14,940 --> 00:21:17,859
- Me, too.
- I've had life-altering experiences

454
00:21:18,133 --> 00:21:19,309
in those hallowed walls.
Oh, my...

455
00:21:19,434 --> 00:21:21,487
Taxi Driver...
And Rang Bull.

456
00:21:21,701 --> 00:21:23,409
The Scorsese festival. The best...

457
00:21:23,534 --> 00:21:26,145
- I go every year at Christmas.
- Me, too.

458
00:21:26,667 --> 00:21:27,975
I ca...
This... I can't deal with this.

459
00:21:28,100 --> 00:21:29,843
Like, we've probably
been standing in line

460
00:21:29,968 --> 00:21:31,706
