00:23:48,887 --> 00:23:50,344
No, no, it's, it's totally fine.

509
00:23:51,681 --> 00:23:53,973
Come over, please.

510
00:24:00,065 --> 00:24:02,342
Is Riley okay?

511
00:24:02,525 --> 00:24:05,309
Yeah, she's just...
she's just had a rough day.

512
00:24:05,434 --> 00:24:07,986
Um, do you mind if
I help you out tomorrow?

513
00:24:08,156 --> 00:24:10,042
No, of course not.

514
00:24:10,167 --> 00:24:12,365
Riley obviously needs
you more than I do.

515
00:24:12,534 --> 00:24:14,834
Thanks, Violet.

516
00:24:19,567 --> 00:24:21,576
Ella said
the photographer was trying

517
00:24:21,701 --> 00:24:23,476
to strip away my inhibitions.

518
00:24:23,601 --> 00:24:24,776
I don't know.

519
00:24:24,901 --> 00:24:27,567
Sounds like she took you
for a rough ride out there.

520
00:24:29,033 --> 00:24:30,209
I moved where she wanted,

521
00:24:30,334 --> 00:24:32,309
I looked where she wanted,
I did everything she said.

522
00:24:32,434 --> 00:24:34,667
I mean...

523
00:24:36,234 --> 00:24:38,434
Auggie, I even took my shirt off.

524
00:24:39,367 --> 00:24:41,567
How'd that go?

525
00:24:42,834 --> 00:24:43,809
How do you think?

526
00:24:44,754 --> 00:24:47,242
I'm a schoolteacher pretending to be
some sort of supermodel.

527
00:24:47,903 --> 00:24:48,776
Yeah, well, you're allowed to want

528
00:24:48,901 --> 00:24:50,509
more than one thing in life, Riley.

529
00:24:50,634 --> 00:24:54,142
Jonah is going to hate me
for giving up that money.

530
00:24:54,267 --> 00:24:56,709
Riley,
I don't know if you know this,

531
00:24:56,834 --> 00:24:59,601
but it's kind of
impossible to hate you.

532
00:25:00,934 --> 00:25:02,634
He'll understand.

533
00:25:05,078 --> 00:25:07,380
I just had to get out of there.
She just kept

534
00:25:08,017 --> 00:25:10,758
pushing me to be this reckless,
carefree

535
00:25:10,926 --> 00:25:13,494
kind of person who just throws
caution to the wind.

536
00:25:16,934 --> 00:25:20,133
It's like she was trying to make
me question my choices in life.

537
00:25:26,934 --> 00:25:29,467
You don't think I'm too young
to get married, do you?

538
00:25:31,367 --> 00:25:34,033
I don't think I'm the
right guy to answer that.

539
00:25:46,467 --> 00:25:48,843
You know, um, instead of drinks,

540
00:25:48,968 --> 00:25:51,342
like, if you just want to meet
at your office another day,

541
00:25:51,593 --> 00:25:53,242
my schedule is super loose.

542
00:25:53,367 --> 00:25:56,053
Eh, don't worry about it.
Drinks go on the company card.

543
00:25:56,221 --> 00:25:58,442
You got to love a studio gig.

544
00:25:59,141 --> 00:26:01,423
You've seen Autumn Falls, right?

545
00:26:01,548 --> 00:26:02,659
Three times.

546
00:26:02,784 --> 00:26:05,479
My ex-boyfriend
wrote and directed it.

547
00:26:05,647 --> 00:26:07,064
Kevin Carlyle is your ex-boyfriend?

548
00:26:07,977 --> 00:26:10,916
Andrew plucked him out of
obscurity and made him huge.

549
00:26:12,000 --> 00:26:14,234
You kind of remind me of him.

550
00:26:16,167 --> 00:26:17,809
Thank you.

551
00:26:19,567 --> 00:26:22,376
Look, I got to be honest with you,
Kendra.

552
00:26:22,501 --> 00:26:25,975
I don't know if I can come tonight.

553
00:26:26,100 --> 00:26:27,709
How come?

554
00:26:27,834 --> 00:26:30,809
It's just I...

555
00:26:30,934 --> 00:26:33,342
well, I,
I kind of have some plans already.

556
00:26:33,467 --> 00:26:35,367
So, you know...

557
00:26:37,067 --> 00:26:39,043
All right, well, if
you happen to free up,

558
00:26:39,168 --> 00:26:41,168
You know where I'll be.

559
00:26:50,401 --> 00:26:53,542
Caleb, Muffin, I would hardly
call the shoot a disaster.

560
00:26:53,738 --> 00:26:56,030
Look, I'm sure Jo got
some amazing shots.

561
00:27:00,400 --> 00:27:02,042
Of course I'll work it out.

562
00:27:02,167 --> 00:27:03,703
I always do.

563
00:27:05,501 --> 00:27:07,309
That girl was a waste of my time.

564
00:27:07,502 --> 00:27:09,509
So Riley's no Elle Macpherson.

565
00:27:09,634 --> 00:27:10,908
Not like you did her any favors,

566
00:27:11,033 --> 00:27:12,743
constantly reminding her of that.

567
00:27:12,868 --> 00:27:15,075
With amateurs, it's my job
to ruffle their feathers.

568
00:27:15,200 --> 00:27:16,509
Without that little push,

569
00:27:16,634 --> 00:27:18,175
she couldn't even
get off the ground.

570
00:27:18,388 --> 00:27:21,847
Right, and you're the
professional, supposedly.

571
00:27:22,892 --> 00:27:24,975
Maybe you shouldn't
have pushed her so hard.

572
00:27:25,200 --> 00:27:26,434
It's what I do.

573
00:27:26,604 --> 00:27:29,145
Until she's able to tap
into who she really is,

574
00:27:29,315 --> 00:27:31,898
she should stick to the ABC's instead
of selling out for a pair of jeans

575
00:27:32,067 --> 00:27:33,233
and a few thousand bucks.

576
00:27:33,403 --> 00:27:35,875
Selling out?

577
00:27:36,114 --> 00:27:39,442
I'm sorry,
weren't you the one who traded in

578
00:27:39,659 --> 00:27:42,785
the refugee camps for a
12-page spread in Vogue?

579
00:27:45,534 --> 00:27:48,416
Maybe Riley wasn't the only one
posing out there today.

580
00:28:14,486 --> 00:28:18,275
Isn't this bird's nest,
like, the coolest thing ever?

581
00:28:19,574 --> 00:28:21,406
If it wasn't
dive-bombing our doorway.

582
00:28:22,952 --> 00:28:26,036
What were you doing out
here... gauging the pH levels?

583
00:28:26,234 --> 00:28:27,275
No, I was just taking a break.

584
00:28:27,400 --> 00:28:29,539
I've been trying to put
some furniture together.

585
00:28:29,709 --> 00:28:31,576
Right.

586
00:28:31,701 --> 00:28:33,843
I would lend you a hand with that,

587
00:28:33,968 --> 00:28:36,109
but, uh, I have a date with Riley

588
00:28:36,234 --> 00:28:38,006
when she gets back
from her photo shoot.

589
00:28:38,176 --> 00:28:40,275
I think Riley's back already.

590
00:28:40,470 --> 00:28:41,542
No, I'm pretty sure she's not.

591
00:28:41,667 --> 00:28:43,609
She was going to call
me on her way home.

592
00:28:43,734 --> 00:28:46,473
Well, then, maybe your phone's
messed up. She came home

593
00:28:46,667 --> 00:28:49,225
about a half hour ago.
She's probably still at Auggie's.

594
00:28:49,976 --> 00:28:51,876
Sh... she went to Auggie's?

595
00:28:52,001 --> 00:28:54,231
He was supposed to help me
assemble my furniture,

596
00:28:54,434 --> 00:28:56,559
but then she came home
and she was super upset,

597
00:28:56,684 --> 00:28:58,075
so he invited her over.

598
00:28:58,279 --> 00:29:00,070
Wait... did something
happen at the shoot?

599
00:29:00,621 --> 00:29:01,537
No clue.

600
00:29:02,167 --> 00:29:04,042
You know how the two of them are...

601
00:29:04,167 --> 00:29:07,142
like everything's
their little secret.

602
00:29:07,267 --> 00:29:09,075
I should let you

603
00:29:09,249 --> 00:29:11,409
get back to your life.
I promise I won't drag you

604
00:29:11,534 --> 00:29:12,975
into any more of my meltdowns.

605
00:29:13,100 --> 00:29:14,167
Riley, we all have our moments.

606
00:29:14,337 --> 00:29:15,877
We wouldn't be human if we didn't.

607
00:29:20,300 --> 00:29:22,217
Oh, hey, buddy.

608
00:29:23,601 --> 00:29:25,762
Come on in.

609
00:29:25,932 --> 00:29:27,609
I heard you had a big meeting
with a producer today.

610
00:29:27,809 --> 00:29:29,942
How was your meeting?

611
00:29:30,144 --> 00:29:32,310
Please tell me we have
a reason to celebrate.

612
00:29:32,480 --> 00:29:34,676
Yeah, yeah, it went, uh, went great.

613
00:29:34,857 --> 00:29:36,023
That's awesome.

614
00:29:37,402 --> 00:29:39,067
I am so glad you're home.

615
00:29:39,237 --> 00:29:40,442
I'm starving

616
00:29:40,613 --> 00:29:42,946
and in desperate need
of a champagne buzz.

617
00:29:43,116 --> 00:29:45,324
Oh, I guess that means
your shoot went well?

618
00:29:47,203 --> 00:29:50,075
I will tell you all about
it when we get home.

619
00:29:52,801 --> 00:29:54,666
I want to borrow
a bike pump from Auggie.

620
00:29:54,836 --> 00:29:56,167
Meet you back at the ranch?

621
00:29:56,337 --> 00:29:57,919
I'll go dig out those veggie burgers

622
00:29:58,089 --> 00:29:59,546
that have been hiding
in the freezer.

623
00:29:59,716 --> 00:30:00,968
Perfect.

624
00:30:03,978 --> 00:30:05,542
Thanks for the tea,

625
00:30:05,667 --> 00:30:06,554
Anytime.

626
00:30:13,701 --> 00:30:16,771
What's going on here?

627
00:30:16,941 --> 00:30:19,376
What are you talking about?

628
00:30:19,569 --> 00:30:21,476
I'm talking about the hours on end

629
00:30:21,654 --> 00:30:24,320
you spend behind closed
doors with my fiancée.

630
00:30:24,490 --> 00:30:26,476
Riley's shoot didn't go as planned.

631
00:30:26,601 --> 00:30:28,492
She just wanted to talk about it.

632
00:30:28,701 --> 00:30:29,743
And look who was more than happy

633
00:30:29,868 --> 00:30:31,453
to throw a strong
shoulder in her direction.

634
00:30:31,623 --> 00:30:32,871
You were in a meeting, she
didn't want to bother you.

635
00:30:33,067 --> 00:30:34,330
Seriously,

636
00:30:34,501 --> 00:30:35,498
that's all that happened.

637
00:30:35,701 --> 00:30:36,975
Right. So, you're still playing

638
00:30:37,100 --> 00:30:38,501
the "we're just friends" card?

639
00:30:38,701 --> 00:30:40,295
I'm not playing any card, Jonah.

640
00:30:40,465 --> 00:30:42,173
We are just friends.

641
00:30:42,400 --> 00:30:43,673
Really?

642
00:30:43,868 --> 00:30:45,049
Because I saw security footage

643
00:30:45,219 --> 00:30:47,594
of you guys sitting out
in the courtyard acting

644
00:30:47,767 --> 00:30:48,929
like way more

645
00:30:49,133 --> 00:30:49,875
than friendly.

646
00:30:50,058 --> 00:30:51,942
You mean the day after Sydney died?

647
00:30:52,143 --> 00:30:54,242
I was barely holding it together.

648
00:30:54,437 --> 00:30:57,309
Riley was the one person
who would talk to me.

649
00:30:57,482 --> 00:30:59,776
I'm sure it was
the sound of her voice

650
00:30:59,901 --> 00:31:01,774
you found so incredibly consoling.

651
00:31:01,944 --> 00:31:04,652
You're way off base.
I just want you to tell me

652
00:31:04,834 --> 00:31:06,975
that you and Riley have not
crossed the line of friendship.

653
00:31:07,100 --> 00:31:09,008
You know, she always jokes
that you're paranoid.

654
00:31:09,133 --> 00:31:10,442
She's not really joking, is she?

655
00:31:10,620 --> 00:31:12,809
Look, Riley and I have already
talked about what happened,

656
00:31:14,400 --> 00:31:16,289
I think maybe it's
time that you fess up.

657
00:31:16,459 --> 00:31:18,834
She kissed me,
not the other way around.

658
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:23,506
She kissed you?

659
00:31:27,467 --> 00:31:28,875
Wha...

660
00:31:29,000 --> 00:31:30,888
Look, I'm talking about...

661
00:31:35,100 --> 00:31:36,400
She kissed you?

662
00:31:37,334 --> 00:31:39,270
It's not what you think.

663
00:31:40,934 --> 00:31:41,734
She was drunk.

664
00:31:42,634 --> 00:31:44,442
She loves you.

665
00:31:44,612 --> 00:31:45,602
Trust me.

666
00:32:08,469 --> 00:32:09,676
So, what should we toast?

667
00:32:09,801 --> 00:32:11,135
To your bright future

668
00:32:11,305 --> 00:32:12,843
as a filmmaker?

669
00:32:12,968 --> 00:32:14,931
Or my terribly short
career as a model?

670
00:32:23,100 --> 00:32:25,567
Okay, you are either really
thirsty or really upset.

671
00:32:27,567 --> 00:32:29,612
Why did you go to Auggie?

672
00:32:31,734 --> 00:32:34,008
Jonah, you were having
the biggest meeting of your career.

673
00:32:34,203 --> 00:32:36,242
I didn't want to burden you
with my modeling woes.

674
00:32:36,367 --> 00:32:38,342
Right, well,
you could have texted me.

675
00:32:38,541 --> 00:32:40,142
I guess it was just...

676
00:32:40,267 --> 00:32:42,126
just easier to go to
Auggie's open door.

677
00:32:43,300 --> 00:32:44,609
What?

678
00:32:44,734 --> 00:32:46,075
This isn't about Auggie,

679
00:32:46,200 --> 00:32:48,042
it's about me,

680
00:32:48,167 --> 00:32:50,109
completely blowing it today.

681
00:32:50,303 --> 00:32:51,409
Ten grand.

682
00:32:51,596 --> 00:32:52,542
Gone.

683
00:32:52,667 --> 00:32:53,609
I mean, I... I showed up,

684
00:32:53,806 --> 00:32:56,743
and... I couldn't follow through.

685
00:32:56,934 --> 00:32:58,542
I really wanted

686
00:32:58,770 --> 00:33:01,144
to do this for you,
Jonah, and I couldn't.

687
00:33:03,316 --> 00:33:05,975
I let you down.

688
00:33:06,100 --> 00:33:07,984
No, you didn't.

689
00:33:08,154 --> 00:33:09,175
You didn't let me down.

690
00:33:09,300 --> 00:33:11,642
At least not because
you ran out on some...

691
00:33:11,767 --> 00:33:13,824
some photo shoot.

692
00:33:15,000 --> 00:33:17,994
I don't care about the money.

693
00:33:18,164 --> 00:33:20,122
You get that, right?

694
00:33:21,234 --> 00:33:23,442
All I care about

695
00:33:23,669 --> 00:33:27,042
is knowing that you're
telling me the truth.

696
00:33:28,966 --> 00:33:31,576
So there's nothing going
on between you two?

697
00:33:33,000 --> 00:33:33,942
Are you... are you

698
00:33:34,138 --> 00:33:34,843
seriously still worried

699
00:33:35,056 --> 00:33:36,175
about Auggie and me?

700
00:33:36,349 --> 00:33:37,676
Nothing has ever happened

701
00:33:37,850 --> 00:33:39,642
between you guys?

702
00:33:41,667 --> 00:33:43,376
Your ring is on

703
00:33:43,564 --> 00:33:44,342
my finger.

704
00:33:44,607 --> 00:33:46,843
You are the only guy
I want to be with.

705
00:33:46,968 --> 00:33:48,442
You want the truth, that's it.

706
00:33:50,601 --> 00:33:52,153
Right.

707
00:33:53,501 --> 00:33:55,157
You sound entirely convinced.

708
00:33:59,497 --> 00:34:01,908
I just gotta get

709
00:34:02,083 --> 00:34:03,309
some air.

710
00:34:03,434 --> 00:34:04,625
Whatever you need to do.

711
00:34:12,934 --> 00:34:15,075
What, are you stalking me now?

712
00:34:15,200 --> 00:34:17,075
David, this is serious.

713
00:34:17,265 --> 00:34:20,409
That must've been thousands
of dollars worth of diamonds.

714
00:34:20,534 --> 00:34:22,442
Not really your problem, is it?

715
00:34:22,567 --> 00:34:24,075
Is it the thrill?

716
00:34:24,200 --> 00:34:26,576
Do you get off on doing this to people?
I see.

717
00:34:26,701 --> 00:34:28,275
First you're my doctor,
now you're my shrink.

718
00:34:28,400 --> 00:34:29,776
David, if you think you need

719
00:34:29,901 --> 00:34:31,609
to go out and take what's not yours,

720
00:34:31,734 --> 00:34:34,409
there's obviously something
missing in your life.

721
00:34:34,534 --> 00:34:37,609
What would you know about that, huh?

722
00:34:37,734 --> 00:34:39,609
That's right.

723
00:34:39,829 --> 00:34:41,109
Miss prim and proper.

724
00:34:41,234 --> 00:34:42,109
The ambitious doctor

725
00:34:42,373 --> 00:34:44,109
who's got it all figured out.

726
00:34:44,234 --> 00:34:45,975
You wouldn't have any
idea what it's like

727
00:34:46,100 --> 00:34:48,376
to have to bend
the rules just to get by.

728
00:34:49,567 --> 00:34:51,087
You don't think there are times

729
00:34:51,267 --> 00:34:52,714
when I feel powerless?

730
00:34:52,884 --> 00:34:54,109
When I just want

731
00:34:54,343 --> 00:34:56,342
to close my eyes and pretend
that I was somebody else?

732
00:34:56,512 --> 00:34:57,975
You know what?

733
00:34:58,222 --> 00:35:01,181
It doesn't mean I go out
and victimize people.

734
00:35:02,935 --> 00:35:04,709
They're not victims.

735
00:35:04,834 --> 00:35:06,809
The people that I target...

736
00:35:06,934 --> 00:35:08,242
white-collar criminals.

737
00:35:08,367 --> 00:35:10,309
Scum of the Earth.
Just like my father.

738
00:35:10,434 --> 00:35:13,275
What does this have to do
with Dr. Mancini?

739
00:35:13,400 --> 00:35:14,609
My dad's not

740
00:35:14,734 --> 00:35:16,476
the miracle worker that you
and your med school buddies

741
00:35:16,601 --> 00:35:17,905
put on a pedestal, I'm sorry.

742
00:35:18,075 --> 00:35:20,908
Well, you know what, David?

743
00:35:21,033 --> 00:35:22,908
No father's perfect.

744
00:35:23,033 --> 00:35:25,997
He never had an interest in
being my father, Laur.

745
00:35:26,167 --> 00:35:29,008
You know, the idea of a... of
trust fund is almost laughable

746
00:35:29,211 --> 00:35:30,542
considering he's done
everything in his power

747
00:35:30,667 --> 00:35:32,337
to forget I even exist.

748
00:35:34,467 --> 00:35:36,709
Well, I'm sorry.

749
00:35:36,928 --> 00:35:38,709
I'm sorry he let you down.

750
00:35:38,888 --> 00:35:40,175
You didn't deserve it.

751
00:35:40,300 --> 00:35:41,179
But stealing?

752
00:35:41,349 --> 00:35:43,142
Come on, David,

753
00:35:43,267 --> 00:35:45,183
that's not how to get back at him.

754
00:35:47,267 --> 00:35:49,242
Maybe you're right.

755
00:35:49,523 --> 00:35:52,142
But it does allow to loan money
to my friends, doesn't it?

756
00:35:52,360 --> 00:35:55,376
David, do you think I want

757
00:35:55,571 --> 00:35:56,709
anything to do with your money

758
00:35:56,834 --> 00:35:59,114
now that I know where
it comes from, huh?

759
00:36:02,400 --> 00:36:05,328
So, where's your moral
compass pointing to now?

760
00:36:06,868 --> 00:36:07,830
Police?

761
00:36:08,000 --> 00:36:10,333
My old man?

762
00:36:10,503 --> 00:36:14,743
I'm going to do you
the biggest favor of your life.

763
00:36:14,868 --> 00:36:16,756
I'm going to keep it between us.

764
00:36:16,934 --> 00:36:19,576
And in return,

765
00:36:19,701 --> 00:36:22,054
you're never going to steal again.

766
00:36:25,734 --> 00:36:27,609
Go ahead.

767
00:36:27,734 --> 00:36:28,936
Answer it.

768
00:37:06,467 --> 00:37:07,473
Still need a hand?

769
00:37:07,643 --> 00:37:09,908
I wasn't expecting you to show up.

770
00:37:10,104 --> 00:37:11,809
Yeah, sorry I had to bail earlier.

771
00:37:11,934 --> 00:37:13,142
It's cool. Building

772
00:37:13,315 --> 00:37:16,399
this thing has actually
been kind of therapeutic.

773
00:37:16,569 --> 00:37:20,653
Really? 'Cause that's exactly
what I'm looking for right now.

774
00:37:20,823 --> 00:37:22,990
Are you okay?

775
00:37:24,184 --> 00:37:27,442
Yeah, just my sponsor'not
answering his phone.

776
00:37:27,663 --> 00:37:29,342
I'll be fine. I just

777
00:37:29,540 --> 00:37:32,309
think putting
my hands to work would...

778
00:37:32,434 --> 00:37:34,333
help clear my mind.

779
00:37:34,534 --> 00:37:36,419
Great.

780
00:37:36,601 --> 00:37:38,509
So...

781
00:37:38,634 --> 00:37:40,214
what are we making?

782
00:37:40,400 --> 00:37:42,376
My new bed.

783
00:37:42,501 --> 00:37:45,094
Your new bed.

784
00:37:49,018 --> 00:37:49,942
Let's do this.

785
00:37:50,144 --> 00:37:50,893
All right.

786
00:37:52,033 --> 00:37:53,501
Oh, these...

787
00:38:48,202 --> 00:38:50,910
It's your favorite photographer.

788
00:38:51,080 --> 00:38:52,743
I couldn't

789
00:38:52,957 --> 00:38:54,843
believe when I looked your address.

790
00:38:54,968 --> 00:38:56,874
I used to live in
this very building.

791
00:38:57,044 --> 00:38:58,875
Are you serious?

792
00:39:00,033 --> 00:39:02,421
Right over there.

793
00:39:02,591 --> 00:39:05,841
A lot of memories in this place.

794
00:39:06,033 --> 00:39:07,886
A lot of them I'd rather forget.

795
00:39:09,300 --> 00:39:11,097
I noticed someone still
rides a motorcycle.

796
00:39:11,267 --> 00:39:12,234
Is that your fiance's?

797
00:39:15,334 --> 00:39:17,186
Someone else, actually.

798
00:39:19,334 --> 00:39:21,142
Listen, I came by to tell you

799
00:39:21,318 --> 00:39:23,642
that you kind of hit
a nerve with me today,

800
00:39:23,767 --> 00:39:25,275
when you told me to go to hell.

801
00:39:25,447 --> 00:39:26,975
Look, you were just doing your job.

802
00:39:27,100 --> 00:39:28,656
I was totally out of my element...

803
00:39:28,834 --> 00:39:29,576
No, but you were right.

804
00:39:29,827 --> 00:39:32,509
I told you to set yourself free,

805
00:39:32,705 --> 00:39:36,609
and maybe it's time
I take my own advice.

806
00:39:36,792 --> 00:39:39,175
Does that mean you're thinking
about going back to Darfur?

807
00:39:39,378 --> 00:39:41,242
Actually, I was thinking
of heading south for a bit,

808
00:39:41,422 --> 00:39:43,642
to bring some media attention to
the food shortage

809
00:39:43,841 --> 00:39:45,676
in Latin America.

810
00:39:45,801 --> 00:39:49,094
Well, you're obvious
the right woman for the job.

811
00:39:50,701 --> 00:39:53,609
You have a gift of exposing
things in your photos

812
00:39:53,809 --> 00:39:56,308
that most people are afraid
to look at in real life.

813
00:39:56,478 --> 00:39:58,342
It comes with a big pay cut.

814
00:39:58,467 --> 00:40:00,142
Well, if it makes
you feel any better,

815
00:40:00,316 --> 00:40:02,941
you kind of got through to me, too.

816
00:40:05,767 --> 00:40:07,609
Maybe I have closed myself off.

817
00:40:07,823 --> 00:40:11,532
Maybe I need to be
a little more open-minded.

818
00:40:13,667 --> 00:40:16,412
You know, when I was your age,
I was engaged.

819
00:40:16,582 --> 00:40:18,376
After I left him,

820
00:40:18,501 --> 00:40:20,751
that's when my real life kicked in.

821
00:40:22,868 --> 00:40:26,342
How did you know it was
the right thing to do?

822
00:40:26,550 --> 00:40:29,051
I didn't.

823
00:40:32,306 --> 00:40:34,309
I almost forgot.

824
00:40:34,434 --> 00:40:35,931
Listen,
don't worry about how today ended.

825
00:40:36,133 --> 00:40:37,809
Anton, he saw that last photo.

826
00:40:38,020 --> 00:40:40,603
He said he's never seen such
raw emotion in his whole life.

827
00:40:40,773 --> 00:40:43,275
Congratulations.

828
00:40:43,484 --> 00:40:45,900
You are the new face
of Anton V. Jeans.

829
00:40:46,070 --> 00:40:47,652
You're kidding me.

830
00:40:48,906 --> 00:40:50,029
Oh, my God.

831
00:40:54,834 --> 00:40:57,120
Good luck, Riley.

832
00:41:30,634 --> 00:41:32,008
You showed.

833
00:41:32,133 --> 00:41:33,405
I was scared missed you.

834
00:41:33,575 --> 00:41:34,907
What happened to your plans?

835
00:41:35,077 --> 00:41:37,042
Just decided

836
00:41:37,167 --> 00:41:39,329
it was an opportunity
I couldn't pass up.

837
00:41:40,801 --> 00:41:42,248
Can I buy you a drink?

838
00:41:43,424 --> 00:41:44,342
Sure.

